# Cursor Rules for CodeSmash Client

## Metadata Requirements

### Page Metadata
Every page component must export metadata using Next.js Metadata API:

- **Server Components**: Export `metadata` object directly
- **Client Components**: Cannot export metadata (use parent layout or route segment)
- **Template**: The root layout uses template `"%s | CodeSmash"` for all pages

### Implementation Pattern

```typescript
// For Server Components (page.tsx without "use client")
import type { Metadata } from "next"

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: "Page Title",
  description: "Page description that describes the purpose and content",
}

export default function Page() {
  // Component code
}
```

### Metadata Guidelines
1. **Title**: Short, descriptive page title (will be formatted as "Title | CodeSmash")
2. **Description**: Clear description of page content and purpose (150-160 characters ideal)
3. **Client Components**: If page uses "use client", create a parent layout.tsx for metadata
4. **Dynamic Routes**: Use `generateMetadata` function for dynamic content

### Examples

**Home Page:**
```typescript
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: "Home",
  description: "Challenge your friends in real-time coding duels.",
}
```

**Battle Page:**
```typescript
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: "Battle",
  description: "Compete in a real-time 1v1 coding battle.",
}
```

## Enforcement
- All new pages MUST include metadata
- Metadata MUST follow the pattern above
- Descriptions MUST be meaningful and SEO-friendly

